LAGOS – Honourable Ganiyu Johnson, lawmaker representing Oshodi/Isolo constituency 2 at the lower chamber of the National Assembly has felicitated with the national leader of All Progressives Congress  (APC),  Asiwaju Bola Tinubu  on his 70th birthday anniversary. A congratulatory letter which the lawmaker he personally signed and made available to journalists on Tuesday stated that Tinubu has demonstrated exceptional courage, steadfast commitment and abiding faith in the enthronement of Democracy not only in Lagos State and the South-West region of the country but in the entire country. Johnson maintained that Asiwaju has a wealth of experience which Nigerians can continue to tap from, stressing that the national leader of the APC is a detrabalised Nigeria, a nationalist who has the interest and unity of Nigeria at heart. While praying to God to grant the celebrant good heath,  long life and wisdom to continue to add his quota to nation building, Johnson said, “I join you, your family, friends and well-wishers to thank the Almighty God for the life of fulfillment and uncommon accomplishment which you have been blessed you with. “It is on record that you have demonstrated exceptional courage, steadfast commitment and abiding faith in the enthronement of democracy not only in Lagos State, South-West region of gbe country but in the whole nation. It is also gratifying to note that you stand ready to continue to avail us of your wise counsel at all times.” “On behalf of my family, the constituents of Oshodi/Isolo Federal Constituency 2, it is my pleasure to congratulate you on this milestone and wish you many more years of fulfillment,” the message further reads.